# Safety Rules

## Testing

- Unit test coverage thresholds: lines 100%, statements 100%, branches 100%, functions 98.5%. Never lower them.
- E2E coverage thresholds: all 100%. Never lower them.
- If adding new UI code, add corresponding unit and/or E2E tests.
- Use `/* v8 ignore next */` sparingly and only for genuinely unreachable defensive branches. Document why.

## Landing Page

- `public/landing.html` is a static SEO page served at `/`. It has its own subscribe form that calls `POST /api/subscribe` on the backend.
- Do not assume it's unused. Do not remove or modify it without confirmation.
- Changes to `landing.html` may affect SEO (meta tags, structured data, canonical URL).

## API Base

- Dev: `http://127.0.0.1:5000/api` | Prod: `https://api.xlsvc.jsilverman.ca/api`
- Defined in `src/apiBase.js`. Both environments use the `/api` path prefix.
- If changing API URLs, coordinate with the backend repo.

## Build & Deploy

- Vite builds to `dist/`. Deploy process moves React files to `/app/` subfolder, landing page stays at root.
- `base` in `vite.config.js` is `/app/` for production, `/` for dev/E2E. Don't change without understanding the deploy script.
